OpenOffice.org add-in

  This module demonstrates how GeoAPI services can be used from a complex software like
  {{{http://www.openoffice.org}OpenOffice.org}}. This add-in adds the following formulas
  to the Calc software, which can be used in spreadsheets for performing coordinate operations:

*--------------------+---------------------------+-------------------------------------+-------------------------*
|| OOo Formulas     || Java method              || Parameters                         || Supported by this demo ||
*--------------------+---------------------------+-------------------------------------+-------------------------*
| CRS.DESCRIPTION    | getDescription            | EPSG code                           | yes but incomplete      |
*--------------------+---------------------------+-------------------------------------+-------------------------*
| CRS.SCOPE          | getScope                  | EPSG code                           | no, see other impl.     |
*--------------------+---------------------------+-------------------------------------+-------------------------*
| CRS.VALID.AREA     | getValidArea              | EPSG code                           | no, see other impl.     |
*--------------------+---------------------------+-------------------------------------+-------------------------*
| CRS.BOUNDING.BOX   | getBoundingBox            | EPSG code                           | no, see other impl.     |
*--------------------+---------------------------+-------------------------------------+-------------------------*
| CRS.REMARKS        | getRemarks                | EPSG code                           | no, see other impl.     |
*--------------------+---------------------------+-------------------------------------+-------------------------*
| CRS.AXIS           | getAxis                   | EPSG code, dimension                | yes but incomplete      |
*--------------------+---------------------------+-------------------------------------+-------------------------*
| CRS.PARAMETER      | getParameter              | EPSG code, parameter name           | no, see other impl.     |
*--------------------+---------------------------+-------------------------------------+-------------------------*
| CRS.WKT            | getWKT                    | EPSG code, authority name           | no, see other impl.     |
*--------------------+---------------------------+-------------------------------------+-------------------------*
| TRANSFORM.WKT      | getTransformWKT           | EPSG code, authority name           | no, see other impl.     |
*--------------------+---------------------------+-------------------------------------+-------------------------*
| TRANSFORM.ACCURACY | getAccuracy               | source CRS, target CRS              | no, see other impl.     |
*--------------------+---------------------------+-------------------------------------+-------------------------*
| TRANSFORM.COORD    | getTransformedCoordinates | coordinates, source CRS, target CRS | yes                     |
*--------------------+---------------------------+-------------------------------------+-------------------------*

  This demo uses the {{{../geotk-proj4/index.html}Proj.4}} binding, which requires a native
  library. However implementors are free to distribute this add-in with the <<<geotk-proj4.jar>>>
  file replaced by their own implementation. See {{{./replace.html}here}} for instructions.

  Users should be able to switch implementations as long as the add-ins use the same programmatic
  names for formulas (<<<org.opengis.openoffice.XReferencing.getFoo>>>) and the same parameters.


* Demo spreadsheets

  The following files can be opened in OpenOffice.org after the demo add-in, or an alternative
  implementation listed below, has been installed:

